The paper discusses the application of Reinforcement Learning (RL) to autonomous driving, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks to handle the continuous action space challenge suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The focus on control strategy and trajectory tracking in dynamic situations indicates that the paper may also be relevant to Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of simulation platforms and embedded properties of real-time vehicle interactions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV).
